


GitHub repository (name as Cloudcredits)

DevOps project:

	Project 1: Web Server Using Docker
	Objective: Containerize a simple web application using Docker and deploy it.

              		Docker Desktop Downloaded
              		wsl --update (PowerShell)
              		Installed Docker Desktop  {https://docs.docker.com/desktop/setup/install/windows-install/}
		
	1. Prerequisites:
			Install Docker (Docker Installation Guide).
			Basic knowledge of Git and a GitHub account.
	2. Application Setup:
			Create a simple web app (e.g., a "Hello World" HTML page or a Python Flask app).
			Example Flask app (app.py):

			from flask import Flask  
			app = Flask(__name__)  
			  
			@app.route('/')  
			def hello():  
			    return "Hello from Dockerized Flask!"  
			  
			if __name__ == '__main__':  
			    app.run(host='0.0.0.0', port=5000)  

		Create a requirements.txt file with Flask==2.0.1.

	3. Containerization:
			Create a Dockerfile:
	
  	Project 2: Implement a CI/CD Pipeline
